(1, 'Vegan Kale Pesto Pasta', 'Tracey Raye', '10mins', '10 Minutes', 'Easy', '4', '13', '5', 'Whizz up kale, pumpkin seeds, basil and garlic to make this easy kale pesto. It\'s perfect stirred through wholemeal spaghetti for a healthy vegan meal', '{\"fat\": \"22\", \"kcal\": \"537\", \"salt\": \"0.1\", \"carbs\": \"60\", \"fibre\": \"13\", \"sugars\": \"1\", \"protein\": \"18\", \"saturates\": \"3\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>150g&nbsp;kale</li>\r\n	<li>small bunch of&nbsp;basil</li>\r\n	<li>1 small&nbsp;garlic clove</li>\r\n	<li>3 tbsp&nbsp;pumpkin seeds</li>\r\n	<li>5 tbsp&nbsp;extra virgin olive oil</li>\r\n	<li>3 tbsp&nbsp;nutritional yeast</li>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;lemon,&nbsp;zested and juiced</li>\r\n	<li>350g&nbsp;wholemeal spaghetti</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Bring a pan of water to the boil. Cook the kale for 30 secs, drain and transfer to a bowl of ice-cold water for 5 mins. Drain again and pat dry with kitchen paper.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Put the basil, garlic, seeds, oil, nutritional yeast, lemon juice and zest, and drained kale in a&nbsp;food processor. Blitz until smooth, then season. Loosen with a splash of water, if it&rsquo;s too thick.</li>\r\n	<li>Cook the pasta following pack instructions, then toss with the pesto and serve.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 10:22:38', NULL),
(2, 'Easy Roast Beef', 'James Martin', '15mins', '60 minutes', 'Easy', '4', '77', '49', 'This easy roast beef recipe with carrots and a simple gravy is ideal for a stunning Sunday dinner for the family. It takes just 15 minutes to prepare', '{\"fat\": \"32\", \"kcal\": \"546\", \"salt\": \"0.65\", \"carbs\": \"15\", \"fibre\": \"4\", \"sugars\": \"11\", \"protein\": \"52\", \"saturates\": \"14\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>1 tsp&nbsp;plain flour</li>\r\n	<li>1 tsp&nbsp;mustard powder</li>\r\n	<li>950g&nbsp;beef&nbsp;top rump joint&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;onion,&nbsp;cut into 8 wedges</li>\r\n	<li>500g&nbsp;carrots,&nbsp;halved lengthways</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>For the gravy</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp&nbsp;plain flour</li>\r\n	<li>250ml&nbsp;beef stock</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Heat oven to 240C/220C fan/gas 9.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Mix 1 tsp plain flour and 1 tsp mustard powder with some seasoning, then rub all over the 950g beef top rump joint.</li>\r\n	<li>Put 1 onion, cut into 8 wedges, and 500g carrots, halved lengthways, into a roasting tin and sit the beef on top, then cook for 20 mins.</li>\r\n	<li>Reduce oven to 190C/170C fan/gas 5 and continue to cook the beef for 30 mins if you like it rare, 40 mins for medium and 1 hr for well done.</li>\r\n	<li>Remove the beef and carrots from the oven, place onto warm plates or platters and cover with foil to keep warm.</li>\r\n	<li>Let the beef rest for 30 mins while you turn up the oven to cook your Yorkshire puds and finish the potatoes.</li>\r\n	<li>For the gravy, put the tin with all the meat juices and onions back onto the hob.</li>\r\n	<li>Stir in 1 tbsp plain flour, scraping all the stuck bits off the bottom of the tin. Cook for 30 seconds, then slowly stir in 250ml beef stock, little by little.</li>\r\n	<li>Bubble to a nice gravy, season, then serve with the beef, carved into slices, carrots and all the other trimmings.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 11:33:41', NULL),
(3, 'Chicken, Leek & Cider Pie', 'Diana Henry', '30 minutes', '95 minutes', 'More Effort', '4', '27', '12', 'There\'s nothing nicer than a warming chicken pie with crisp, golden-brown puff pastry and creamy, rich sauce', '{\"fat\": \"65\", \"kcal\": \"1041\", \"salt\": \"1.8\", \"carbs\": \"55\", \"fibre\": \"7\", \"sugars\": \"13\", \"protein\": \"51\", \"saturates\": \"33\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>60g&nbsp;unsalted butter</li>\r\n	<li>60g&nbsp;plain flour</li>\r\n	<li>250ml&nbsp;dry cider</li>\r\n	<li>250ml&nbsp;full-fat milk</li>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp&nbsp;Dijon mustard</li>\r\n	<li>juice 1/2 lemon</li>\r\n	<li>2 tbsp&nbsp;cr&egrave;me fra&icirc;che</li>\r\n	<li>3&nbsp;medium leeks,&nbsp;sliced into rings</li>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;large apple,&nbsp;peeled, cored and sliced</li>\r\n	<li>500g&nbsp;cooked chicken,&nbsp;torn or cut into pieces</li>\r\n	<li>50g&nbsp;extra mature cheddar,&nbsp;grated</li>\r\n	<li>375g&nbsp;puff pastry</li>\r\n	<li>2&nbsp;egg yolks,&nbsp;beaten with 2 tsp milk (to make an egg wash)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Melt 40g of the butter in a&nbsp;saucepan&nbsp;and add the flour. Stir this over a medium-low heat for 1 min to make a roux. Remove from the heat and start adding the cider a little at a time. Mix well with a wooden spoon to ensure there are no lumps. Keep stirring until all the cider has been added, then add the milk in the same way. Season, return the pan to the heat and, stirring continuously, bring to the boil. The mixture will thicken considerably and, once it has come to the boil, reduce the heat and simmer for about 3 mins. Stir in the mustard, lemon juice and cr&egrave;me fra&icirc;che , and taste for seasoning.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Melt the rest of the butter in a frying pan and gently fry the leeks and the apples for 5 mins. Add 2 tbsp of water, season, cover and cook over a low heat for 8-10 mins until tender. If there are lots of juices, increase the heat to reduce them.</li>\r\n	<li>Add half the cheese to the sauce, then bring to the boil. Reduce the heat and gently stir in the leeks and apples and taste &ndash; you may want to add more mustard or lemon juice. Cool and chill the sauce until you&rsquo;re ready to assemble the pie.</li>\r\n	<li>Stir the chicken into the cooled sauce. Put the mixture into a 25 x 20cm pie dish or a round dish measuring 25cm across (with a 1.3 litre capacity). Sprinkle with the rest of the cheese and leave to cool completely.</li>\r\n	<li>Heat oven to 200C/180C fan/ gas 6. On a lightly floured surface, roll the pastry out to the thickness of a 50 p coin. Cut off a strip the same width as the lip of the pie dish. Wet the lip and press this strip onto it. Brush the strip with water and lay the rest of the pastry on top. Press the pastry lid onto the pastry strip, then cut off the excess. Crimp the edges and use the remaining pastry to decorate the top of the pie. Make three small slits in the pastry near the middle to let the steam escape. Brush the top with the egg mixture and bake in the oven for 30 -40 mins, until the pastry is a deep golden colour and puffed up. Serve immediately.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 12:03:28', NULL),
(4, 'Gnocchi cacio e pepe', 'Esther Clark', '2miuntes', '5minutes', 'Easy', '2', '22', '11', 'Enjoy a comforting bowl of gnocchi with parmesan and black pepper. It\'s simple but utterly delicious – and the best part is, it only takes seven minutes to make', '{\"fat\": \"21\", \"kcal\": \"424\", \"salt\": \"1.6\", \"carbs\": \"41\", \"fibre\": \"4\", \"sugars\": \"2\", \"protein\": \"15\", \"saturates\": \"14\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>300g&nbsp;gnocchi</li>\r\n	<li>2 tbsp&nbsp;unsalted butter</li>\r\n	<li>60g&nbsp;parmesan&nbsp;or vegetarian alternative, finely grated</li>\r\n	<li>2 tsp&nbsp;black pepper</li>\r\n	<li>salad leaves&nbsp;, to serve (optional)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Cook the gnocchi in a large pan of lightly salted, boiling water. Drain and reserve 200ml of the&nbsp;cooking water.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Heat the butter in a large&nbsp;frying pan. Add the gnocchi, cheese and pepper as well as 150ml of the cooking water, raise the heat a little and stir vigorously until melted and the gnocchi is well coated. Pour in more of the reserved water if you like it saucier. Season with a little salt. Transfer the gnocchi to bowls and serve with a mixed salad, if you like.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 15:39:09', NULL),
(5, 'Cheesy Mushroom Omelette', 'Good Food team', '5mins', '10 Minutes', 'Easy', '1', '24', '11', 'Whip up a tasty omelette with this recipe', '{\"fat\": \"33\", \"kcal\": \"391\", \"salt\": \"0.9\", \"carbs\": \"0.3\", \"fibre\": \"0.7\", \"sugars\": \"0.2\", \"protein\": \"22\", \"saturates\": \"10\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp&nbsp;olive oil</li>\r\n	<li>handful&nbsp;button or chestnut mushrooms,&nbsp;sliced</li>\r\n	<li>25g&nbsp;vegetarian cheddar,&nbsp;grated</li>\r\n	<li>small handful&nbsp;parsley&nbsp;leaves, roughly chopped</li>\r\n	<li>2&nbsp;eggs,&nbsp;beaten</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Heat the olive oil in a small non-stick frying pan. Tip in the mushrooms and fry over a high heat, stirring occasionally for 2-3 mins until golden. Lift out of the pan into a bowl and mix with the cheese and parsley.</li>\r\n	<li>Place the pan back on the heat and swirl the eggs into it. Cook for 1 min or until set to your liking, swirling with a fork now and again.</li>\r\n	<li>Spoon the mushroom mix over one half of the omelette. Using a spatula or palette knife, flip the omelette over to cover the mushrooms. Cook for a few moments more, lift onto a plate and serve with oven chips and salad.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '2022-05-15 16:04:06', NULL),
(6, 'Cheese & Ham Souffléd Omelette', 'Silvana Franco', '10mins', '10 Minutes', 'More Effort', '1', '12', '8', 'This fluffy and filling meal for one uses up leftover ham or gammon and makes a great brunch served with baked beans', '{\"fat\": \"39\", \"kcal\": \"507\", \"salt\": \"3.48\", \"carbs\": \"1\", \"fibre\": \"0.1\", \"sugars\": \"1\", \"protein\": \"39\", \"saturates\": \"16\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>50g&nbsp;grated gruy&egrave;re&nbsp;or cheddar</li>\r\n	<li>2&nbsp;slices roughly torn ham&nbsp;or gammon</li>\r\n	<li>2&nbsp;eggs&nbsp;, whites and yolks separated</li>\r\n	<li>1 tsp&nbsp;Dijon mustard</li>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp&nbsp;chopped fresh dill&nbsp;or basil</li>\r\n	<li>splash&nbsp;olive oil</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Mix most of the cheese with the ham or gammon, egg yolks, mustard, herbs and some seasoning. Whisk egg whites until stiff. Using a rubber spatula, gently fold the whites into the yolk mixture until evenly mixed.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Heat a splash of olive oil in a small non-stick frying pan. Pour mixture into the pan and cook for 4 mins until the underside is set and browned. Sprinkle over the remaining cheese and grill for 2 mins until cheese is bubbling and golden.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 16:14:28', NULL),
(7, 'Spiced Carrot & Lentil Soup', 'Jane Hornby', '10 mins', '10 Mins', 'Easy', '4', '1212', '793', 'A delicious, spicy blend packed full of iron and low in fat to boot. It\'s ready in under half an hour, or can be made in a slow cooker', '{\"fat\": \"7\", \"kcal\": \"238\", \"salt\": \"0.25\", \"carbs\": \"34\", \"fibre\": \"5\", \"sugars\": \"0.1\", \"protein\": \"11\", \"saturates\": \"1\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>2 tsp&nbsp;cumin seeds</li>\r\n	<li>pinch&nbsp;chilli flakes</li>\r\n	<li>2 tbsp&nbsp;olive oil</li>\r\n	<li>600g&nbsp;carrots,&nbsp;washed and coarsely grated (no need to peel)</li>\r\n	<li>140g&nbsp;split red lentils</li>\r\n	<li>1l&nbsp;hot vegetable stock&nbsp;(from a cube is fine)</li>\r\n	<li>125ml&nbsp;milk&nbsp;(to make it dairy-free)</li>\r\n	<li>plain yogurt&nbsp;and naan bread, to serve</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Heat a large saucepan and dry-fry 2 tsp&nbsp;cumin seeds and a pinch of chilli flakes for 1 min, or until they start to jump around the pan and release their aromas.</li>\r\n	<li>Scoop out about half with a spoon and set aside. Add 2 tbsp olive&nbsp;oil, 600g coarsely grated carrots, 140g split red lentils, 1l hot vegetable stock and 125ml milk to the pan and bring to the boil.</li>\r\n	<li>Simmer for 15 mins until the lentils have swollen and softened.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 16:22:39', NULL),
(8, 'One-pan Salmon with Roast Asparagus', 'Barney Desmazery', '20mins', '50mins', 'Easy', '2', '472', '271', 'For an easy side dish to complement a spring roast, just cook this recipe without the salmon', '{\"fat\": \"25\", \"kcal\": \"483\", \"salt\": \"0.24\", \"carbs\": \"34\", \"fibre\": \"3\", \"sugars\": \"6\", \"protein\": \"33\", \"saturates\": \"4\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>400g&nbsp;new potato,&nbsp;halved if large</li>\r\n	<li>2 tbsp&nbsp;olive oil</li>\r\n	<li>8&nbsp;asparagus&nbsp;spears, trimmed and halved</li>\r\n	<li>2&nbsp;handfuls cherry tomatoes</li>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp&nbsp;balsamic vinegar</li>\r\n	<li>2&nbsp;salmon fillets,&nbsp;about 140g/5oz each</li>\r\n	<li>handful&nbsp;basil leaves</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Heat oven to 220C/fan 200C/gas 7. Tip the potatoes and 1 tbsp of olive oil into an&nbsp;ovenproof dish, then roast the potatoes for 20 mins until starting to brown. Toss the asparagus in with the potatoes, then return to the oven for 15 mins.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Throw in the cherry tomatoes and vinegar and nestle the salmon amongst the vegetables. Drizzle with the remaining oil and return to the oven for a final 10-15 mins until the salmon is cooked. Scatter over the basil leaves and serve everything scooped straight from the dish.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 16:33:06', NULL),
(9, 'Pea, Mint & Spring Onion Soup with Parmesan Biscuits', 'Good Food team', '20mins', '25mins', 'Easy', '6', '49', '51', 'The parmesan \'tuiles\' make this soup stylish enough for entertaining – but they take just a few minutes to make', '{\"fat\": \"9\", \"kcal\": \"213\", \"salt\": \"0.72\", \"carbs\": \"20\", \"fibre\": \"8\", \"sugars\": \"8\", \"protein\": \"15\", \"saturates\": \"4\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp olive oil</li>\r\n	<li>knob of butter</li>\r\n	<li>&frac12; bunch spring onion&nbsp;, sliced, plus a few extra to serve</li>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;potato&nbsp;, cut into small dice</li>\r\n	<li>1l&nbsp;hot vegetable stock</li>\r\n	<li>900g&nbsp;frozen petits pois</li>\r\n	<li>&frac12; small bunch mint&nbsp;, leaves picked, plus a few extra to serve</li>\r\n	<li>85g&nbsp;parmesan&nbsp;(or vegetarian alternative), very finely grated</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Heat the olive oil and butter in a heavy based pan. When foaming, add the spring onions and potato. Gently fry without colouring for about 5 mins. Stir in the stock, bring to the boil and simmer for 10 mins or until the potato is tender.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Stir in the peas, bring to the boil again, then cook for about 3 mins until they are just done. Remove the pan from the heat, add the mint leaves and whizz in a blender or food processor until smooth.</li>\r\n	<li>To make the parmesan biscuits, heat the grill to high. Line a baking sheet with baking parchment and divide the grated parmesan into 6 long strips. Grill for 1 min or until the cheese has melted and is lightly golden. While still warm and a bit flexible, release the biscuits from the baking parchment with a palette or cutlery knife, then cool until firm.</li>\r\n	<li>To serve, heat the soup and divide between 6 bowls. Scatter with mint and sliced spring onions, if you like, and serve with the parmesan biscuits on the side.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 16:40:33', NULL),
(10, 'Tomato & Mascarpone Risotto', 'Esther Clark', '10mins', '30mins', 'Easy', '2', '159', '28', 'Enjoy a comforting bowl of risotto with tomato and mascarpone. It\'s perfect for a Valentine\'s menu, or a special midweek meal', '{\"fat\": \"24\", \"kcal\": \"635\", \"salt\": \"0.3\", \"carbs\": \"86\", \"fibre\": \"6\", \"sugars\": \"14\", \"protein\": \"16\", \"saturates\": \"9\"}', '<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2 tbsp&nbsp;olive oil</li>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;onion&nbsp;, very finely chopped</li>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;large garlic clove&nbsp;, crushed</li>\r\n	<li>175g&nbsp;risotto rice</li>\r\n	<li>400g can&nbsp;cherry tomatoes</li>\r\n	<li>600ml&nbsp;hot vegetable stock</li>\r\n	<li>30g&nbsp;parmesan&nbsp;or vegetarian alternative, grated</li>\r\n	<li>30g&nbsp;mascarpone</li>\r\n	<li>&frac12; small bunch of&nbsp;basil&nbsp;, chopped</li>\r\n</ul>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Heat the oil in a large, heavy-based&nbsp;saucepan. Add the onion along with a pinch of salt, and fry for 10 mins or until beginning to soften and turn translucent, then add the garlic and fry for 1 min. Stir in the rice and cook for 2 mins.</li>\r\n	<li>Tip in the tomatoes and bring to a simmer. Add half the stock, cooking and stirring until absorbed. Add the remaining stock, a ladleful at a time, and cook until the rice is al dente, stirring constantly for around 20 mins.</li>\r\n	<li>Stir through the parmesan, mascarpone and basil, and season to taste. Spoon into bowls to serve.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '2022-05-15 18:03:39', NULL),
(11, 'Chorizo, Potato & Cheese Omelette', 'Good Food team', '8mins', '20mins', 'Easy', '1', '14', '4', 'Whisk up your eggs with Spanish sausage and potato to make a decadent omelette lunch for one', '{\"fat\": \"44\", \"kcal\": \"602\", \"salt\": \"1.8\", \"carbs\": \"15\", \"fibre\": \"1\", \"sugars\": \"2\", \"protein\": \"36\", \"saturates\": \"18\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;small potato&nbsp;, cut into 2cm dice</li>\r\n	<li>1 tsp&nbsp;olive oil</li>\r\n	<li>50g&nbsp;chorizo&nbsp;, chopped</li>\r\n	<li>2-3 eggs</li>\r\n	<li>chopped parsley</li>\r\n	<li>25g&nbsp;grated cheddar</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<p>Cook the potato in boiling water for 8-10 mins or until tender. Drain and allow to steam-dry. Heat oil in an omelette pan, add chorizo and cook for 2 mins. Add the potato and cook for a further 5 mins until the potato starts to crisp. Spoon pan contents out, wipe pan and cook a 2 or 3-egg omelette in the same pan. When almost cooked, scatter with the chorizo and potato, parsley and cheese. Fold the omelette in the pan and cook for 1 min more to melt the cheese.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '2022-05-15 18:05:58', NULL),
(12, 'Chilli Cheese Omelette', 'Good Food team', '10mins', '1min', 'Easy', '1', '10', '9', 'A quick and easy classic with added spice - just six ingredients too', '{\"fat\": \"33\", \"kcal\": \"381\", \"salt\": \"0.86\", \"carbs\": \"0.00\", \"fibre\": \"0.00\", \"sugars\": \"0.00\", \"protein\": \"22\", \"saturates\": \"10\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;spring onion</li>\r\n	<li>a few sprigs of&nbsp;fresh coriander</li>\r\n	<li>2&nbsp;large eggs</li>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp&nbsp;sunflower oil</li>\r\n	<li>&frac12; -1 tsp&nbsp;chopped fresh red chilli&nbsp;, or a generous pinch dried chilli flakes</li>\r\n	<li>25g&nbsp;mild grated cheddar</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Chop the spring onion and coriander quite finely and beat the eggs together with salt and pepper. Heat the oil in a small frying pan then tip in the onion, coriander and chilli and stir round the pan for a second or two so they soften a little. Pour in the eggs and keep them moving until two thirds have scrambled.</li>\r\n	<li>Settle the eggs back down on the base of the pan, scatter over the cheese and cook for about a minute until the omelette is just set and the cheese has melted.</li>\r\n	<li>Carefully fold the omelette using a palette knife and slide from the pan to a serving plate. Eat while the omelette is hot and the cheese still melted.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '2022-05-15 18:10:03', NULL),
(13, 'Smoked Haddock & Leek Risotto', 'Good Food team', '5mins', '35mins', 'Easy', '4', '368', '228', 'There\'s no tedious stirring with this one - just stick it in the oven until creamy and delicious', '{\"fat\": \"10\", \"kcal\": \"444\", \"salt\": \"3.34\", \"carbs\": \"64\", \"fibre\": \"3\", \"sugars\": \"5\", \"protein\": \"29\", \"saturates\": \"5\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>small knob of butter</li>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;large leek,&nbsp;thinly sliced</li>\r\n	<li>300g&nbsp;risotto rice,&nbsp;such as arborio or carnaroli</li>\r\n	<li>700ml&nbsp;fish or vegetable stock</li>\r\n	<li>250ml&nbsp;full-fat milk</li>\r\n	<li>375g&nbsp;undyed smoked haddock,&nbsp;skinned and cut into large chunks</li>\r\n	<li>3 tbsp&nbsp;cr&egrave;me fra&icirc;che</li>\r\n	<li>100g&nbsp;baby spinach</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Heat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas 6. Heat the butter in a large ovenproof dish over a medium heat. Cook the leek for 4-5 mins, stirring regularly, until just tender. Add the rice and stir for a further 2 mins.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Add the stock and milk, bring to the boil and bubble for 5 mins before sitting the haddock on top. Cover with a lid or foil and bake in the oven for 18 mins until the rice is tender.</li>\r\n	<li>Fold in the cr&egrave;me fra&icirc;che and spinach, season with plenty of black pepper, then cover the pan again and leave to rest out of the oven for 3 mins before serving &ndash; the steam will soften the spinach.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 18:13:35', NULL),
(14, 'Basic Omelette Recipe', 'Miriam Nice', '5mins', '5mins', 'Easy', '1', '47', '12', 'Master the omelette with our simple recipe then add the filling of your choice – grated cheese, ham, fresh herbs, mushrooms and smoked salmon are favourites.', '{\"fat\": \"22\", \"kcal\": \"227\", \"salt\": \"0.8\", \"carbs\": \"0.00\", \"fibre\": \"0.00\", \"sugars\": \"0.00\", \"protein\": \"20\", \"saturates\": \"7\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>3&nbsp;eggs,&nbsp;beaten</li>\r\n	<li>1 tsp&nbsp;sunflower oil</li>\r\n	<li>1 tsp&nbsp;butter</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Season the beaten eggs well with salt and pepper. Heat the oil and butter in a&nbsp;non-stick frying pan&nbsp;over a medium-low heat until the butter has melted and is foaming.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Pour the eggs into the pan, tilt the pan ever so slightly from one side to another to allow the eggs to swirl and cover the surface of the pan completely. Let the mixture cook for about 20 seconds then scrape a line through the middle with a spatula.</li>\r\n	<li>Tilt the pan again to allow it to fill back up with the runny egg. Repeat once or twice more until the egg has just set.</li>\r\n	<li>At this point you can fill the omelette with whatever you like &ndash; some grated cheese, sliced ham, fresh herbs, saut&eacute;ed mushrooms or smoked salmon all work well. Scatter the filling over the top of the omelette and fold gently in half with the&nbsp;spatula. Slide onto a plate to serve.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 18:16:34', NULL),
(15, 'Halloumi Burgers', 'Lulu Grimes', '10mins', '10Mins', 'Easy', '4', '33', '5', 'These veggie halloumi burgers in brioche buns are perfect for the whole family. Serve as a quick and easy lunch - they\'re also great on camping holidays', '{\"fat\": \"30\", \"kcal\": \"455\", \"salt\": \"2.7\", \"carbs\": \"25\", \"fibre\": \"3\", \"sugars\": \"8\", \"protein\": \"20\", \"saturates\": \"13\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>250g block&nbsp;halloumi cheese,&nbsp;cut into 8 thick slices</li>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp&nbsp;olive oil</li>\r\n	<li>4&nbsp;brioche buns</li>\r\n	<li>4 tbsp&nbsp;hummus</li>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;large ripe tomato,&nbsp;thinly sliced</li>\r\n	<li>4&nbsp;Butterhead lettuce leaves</li>\r\n	<li>4 tbsp&nbsp;fresh tomato salsa</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Heat a&nbsp;barbecue&nbsp;until&nbsp;the coals are glowing white hot. Brush each side of all the halloumi slices with olive oil and cook them on each side for 2-3 mins or until golden.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Split the brioche buns (toast them very briefly on both sides if you like, but be careful not to burn them) and spread the bottom halves with the hummus. Add some tomato and then the halloumi, then finish with the lettuce and salsa and top with the other half of the bun.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 18:20:25', NULL),
(16, 'Gnocchi & Tomato Bake', 'Good Food team', '5mins', '25mins', 'Easy', '4', '417', '170', 'A comforting veggie main packed with rich Italian flavours', '{\"fat\": \"7\", \"kcal\": \"285\", \"salt\": \"1.64\", \"carbs\": \"50\", \"fibre\": \"4\", \"sugars\": \"8\", \"protein\": \"10\", \"saturates\": \"3\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp&nbsp;olive oil</li>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;onion,&nbsp;chopped</li>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;red pepper,&nbsp;deseeded and finely chopped</li>\r\n	<li>1&nbsp;garlic clove,&nbsp;crushed</li>\r\n	<li>400g can&nbsp;chopped tomatoes</li>\r\n	<li>500g&nbsp;pack gnocchi</li>\r\n	<li>handful&nbsp;basil leaves,&nbsp;torn</li>\r\n	<li>half a ball&nbsp;mozzarella,&nbsp;torn into chunks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Heat grill to high. Heat 1 tbsp olive oil in a large frying pan, then soften 1 chopped onion and 1 finely chopped red pepper for 5 mins.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Stir in 1 crushed garlic clove, fry for 1 min, tip in 400g chopped tomatoes and 500g gnocchi, then bring to a simmer.</li>\r\n	<li>Bubble for 10-15 mins, stirring occasionally, until the gnocchi is soft and the sauce has thickened</li>\r\n	<li>Season, stir through a handful of torn basil leaves, then transfer to a large ovenproof dish.</li>\r\n	<li>Scatter with torn chunks of half a 125g mozzarella ball, then grill for 5-6 mins until the cheese is bubbling and golden.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 18:26:19', NULL),
(17, 'Pasta with Creamy Greens & Lemon', 'Sarah Cook', '2mins', '12mins', 'Easy', '4', '49', '32', 'Try a new topping for your pasta, ready in just 15 minutes', '{\"fat\": \"28\", \"kcal\": \"635\", \"salt\": \"0.54\", \"carbs\": \"75\", \"fibre\": \"7\", \"sugars\": \"7\", \"protein\": \"26\", \"saturates\": \"16\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>350g&nbsp;pasta</li>\r\n	<li>140g&nbsp;broccoli&nbsp;florets</li>\r\n	<li>100g&nbsp;frozen soya beans</li>\r\n	<li>100g&nbsp;frozen peas</li>\r\n	<li>100g&nbsp;mange tout</li>\r\n	<li>150g&nbsp;mascarpone&nbsp;or soft cheese</li>\r\n	<li>zest and juice 1&nbsp;lemon</li>\r\n	<li>85g&nbsp;grated parmesan&nbsp;or vegetarian alternative</li>\r\n	<li>handful&nbsp;basil leaves</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Cook pasta in a very large pan following the pack instructions, adding broccoli florets, frozen soya beans, frozen peas and mange tout for the final 3 mins of cooking time.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Drain, saving a ladleful of the cooking water first, then tip everything back into the pan. Stir in mascarpone or soft cheese, zest and juice 1 lemon, grated Parmesan, a handful basil leaves, some seasoning and a splash of cooking water.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 18:36:54', NULL),
(18, 'Salmon & Spinach with Tartare Cream', 'Good Food team', '5mins', '10Mins', 'Easy', '2', '172', '131', 'Ever-versatile salmon is as popular on our shopping lists as chicken. Make the most of it with this impressive recipe', '{\"fat\": \"20\", \"kcal\": \"321\", \"salt\": \"0.77\", \"carbs\": \"3\", \"fibre\": \"3\", \"sugars\": \"3\", \"protein\": \"32\", \"saturates\": \"5\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>1 tsp&nbsp;sunflower or vegetable oil</li>\r\n	<li>2&nbsp;skinless salmon fillets</li>\r\n	<li>250g&nbsp;bag spinach</li>\r\n	<li>2 tbsp&nbsp;reduced-fat cr&egrave;me fra&icirc;che</li>\r\n	<li>juice &frac12;&nbsp;lemon</li>\r\n	<li>1 tsp&nbsp;caper,&nbsp;drained</li>\r\n	<li>2 tbsp&nbsp;flat-leaf parsley,&nbsp;chopped</li>\r\n	<li>lemon&nbsp;wedges, to serve</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Heat the oil in a pan, season the salmon on both sides, then fry for 4 mins each side until golden and the flesh flakes easily. Leave to rest on a plate while you cook the spinach.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Tip the leaves into the hot pan, season well, then cover and leave to wilt for 1 min, stirring once or twice. Spoon the spinach onto plates, then top with the salmon. Gently heat the cr&egrave;me fra&icirc;che in the pan with a squeeze of the lemon juice, the capers and parsley, then season to taste. Be careful not to let it boil. Spoon the sauce over the fish, then serve with lemon wedges.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 18:39:23', NULL),
(19, 'Brioche', 'Liberty Mendez', '40Mins', '35mins', 'More Effort', '8', '49', '38', 'Make homemade brioche and enjoy with jam or butter for breakfast. It takes a little effort, but the results of this sweet, soft bread are well worth it', '{\"fat\": \"23\", \"kcal\": \"460\", \"salt\": \"1.8\", \"carbs\": \"49\", \"fibre\": \"2\", \"sugars\": \"7\", \"protein\": \"12\", \"saturates\": \"14\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>450g&nbsp;strong white flour</li>\r\n	<li>2 tsp&nbsp;fine sea salt</li>\r\n	<li>50g&nbsp;caster sugar</li>\r\n	<li>7g&nbsp;dried active yeast</li>\r\n	<li>100ml&nbsp;whole milk</li>\r\n	<li>4&nbsp;eggs&nbsp;at room temperature, beaten, plus 1 for egg wash</li>\r\n	<li>190g&nbsp;salted butter&nbsp;, cubed and softened</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Put the flour in a bowl of a&nbsp;stand mixer&nbsp;with a dough hook. Add the salt to one side and sugar to the other. Pour in the yeast to the side with the sugar. Mix each side into the flour with your hands,&nbsp;then mix it all together with the dough hook.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Heat the milk until warm to the touch, but not hot. Mix into the flour mix until combined. With the dough hook on medium, gradually add the eggs and mix for 10 mins.</li>\r\n	<li>Gradually add the softened butter, one or two cubes at a time, until combined. This will take 5-8 mins. Scrape down the sides, the dough will be very soft.</li>\r\n	<li>Scrape the dough into a large bowl, cover with a tea towel and leave for 1 hr 30 mins-2 hrs until doubled in size and well-risen. Once risen, put in the fridge for 1 hr.</li>\r\n	<li>Line the bottom&nbsp;and sides of a 900g loaf tin with baking parchment. Portion the dough into seven equal pieces (the easiest way to do this accurately is to weigh it). Lightly dust a work surface with flour, take a piece of dough and pull each corner into the middle to form a circular shape. With a bit of pressure, push down and roll into ball. Repeat with the six remaining pieces.</li>\r\n	<li>Put the balls into the tin, four&nbsp;on one side and three in the gaps on the other side. Cover with a tea towel and leave to prove for 30-35 mins until almost doubled in size. Heat the oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4. Lightly brush the dough with the egg wash and bake for 30-35 mins until golden and risen. Leave to cool in the tin for 20 mins,&nbsp;then remove and cool completely.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 18:44:02', NULL),
(20, 'Spiced Roast Beef', 'Matt Tebbutt', '10mins', '110mins', 'Easy', '6', '3', '6', 'Matt Tebbutt\'s roast beef combines spices and meltingly tender meat. It\'ll be just as good cold, too', '{\"fat\": \"21\", \"kcal\": \"396\", \"salt\": \"0.68\", \"carbs\": \"1\", \"fibre\": \"0.00\", \"sugars\": \"0.00\", \"protein\": \"51\", \"saturates\": \"9\"}', '<ul>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp&nbsp;juniper berries</li>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp&nbsp;coriander seeds</li>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp&nbsp;black peppercorns</li>\r\n	<li>1 tbsp&nbsp;allspice&nbsp;berries</li>\r\n	<li>2 tbsp&nbsp;olive oil</li>\r\n	<li>2kg-3kg (4lb 8oz-6lb 8oz)&nbsp;topside joint of beef&nbsp;- depending on the amount of leftovers you want</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></p>', '<ol>\r\n	<li>Combine all the spices and &frac12; tbsp salt together in a pestle and mortar. Give everything a good grind, keeping a little of its coarseness. Rub the oil and then the ground spices all over the beef and massage in well. Cover and chill overnight to marinate.<!-- Retain textarea input field if available until form is submitted --></li>\r\n	<li>Next day, heat oven to 190C/170C fan/gas 5. Weigh your joint and roast for 10 mins per 450g for rare meat and 15 mins per 450g for medium, plus an extra 20 mins. Cover and rest for 20 mins while you finish the salads, then slice and serve. Alternatively, roast the beef in the morning and serve at room temperature for dinner.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2022-05-15 18:47:04', NULL);

